In a #small pot{}, combine @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in a small pot over medium-high heat. Add @Riced Cauliflower{12%oz} and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and any excess liquid has absorbed, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

> Save basmati rice for another use.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Core, deseed, and dice @Bell Pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. After ~{5%minutes}, add scallion whites and cook until softened.

> If needed, add splashes of water to help pepper soften.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

While bell pepper cooks, pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper.

Once bell pepper is done, heat another drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Reduce heat under pan to medium.

Add @Tomato Paste{1.5%oz}, @Curry Powder{1%tbsp}, and @Paprika{1%tsp} to pan with chicken. Add a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%tsp} if you like things spicy.

Cook, stirring, until chicken is fully coated and spices are fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Coconut Milk{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, @Butter{1%tbsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> Taste and add more sugar if you like a sweeter curry.

Add bell pepper mixture and @Sour Cream{1.5%tbsp}; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a fork and season with salt and pepper; divide between #bowls{}. Top rice with coconut curry chicken and sprinkle with a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.